den=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 30, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zhr1665702742172.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zhr1665702742172.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zhr1665702742172.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zhr1665702742172\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n Configuring Uniface and Uniface Applications\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__configuring_uniface_and_uniface_applications_96895\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Deploying a Uniface enterprise application is largely a matter of configuring the environment to ensure that all components are running in the appropriate locations and that Uniface is able to find them. Configuration files ensure that the Uniface runtime environment can locate and initialize the application components correctly.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__p_d29756e1_d29757e1_d29758e1\">Assignment files specify paths and protocols, and customize the application. Initialization files customize the user interface and behavior for a specific platform.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__p_d29759e1_d29760e1_d29761e1\">The complexity of the environment determines the complexity of the configuration process. To configure Uniface on a standalone machine is much simpler than to configure a distributed environment with the Uniface Router, Uniface Server, and multiple databases, that also integrates with other technologies.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__p_d29762e1_d29763e1_d29764e1\">The documentation in this collection describes the general use of configuration files, path assignments and redirection, and assignment settings to configure Uniface and Uniface applications.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__table_d3071e1_d3072e1_d3073e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Configuration Files </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15053e1_d15054e1_d15055e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"asd1665702742243.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/asd1665702742243.html\" title=\"Uniface configuration files include assignment files, initialization files, and web application files.\">Configuration Files</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15056e1_d15057e1_d15058e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aoa1665702739697.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aoa1665702739697.html\" title=\"A Uniface assignment file contains one or more assignment settings, which determine the environment of a Uniface application and control aspects of its behavior. Assignment settings can determine the location of application resources and servers, set environment variables, define application logicals, and set Uniface system settings to influence runtime behavior.\">Assignment Files</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15059e1_d15060e1_d15061e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wqb1665702697712.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wqb1665702697712.html\" title=\"Initialization settings are primarily used to configure the user interface of a Uniface application on a specific platform. On all platforms, it is possible define a local initialization file for the application. Settings in the local file usually take precedence over those in the global file or environment variables.\">Initialization Settings and Files</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                        Paths to Resources \n                     </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15062e1_d15063e1_d15064e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sbg1665702735473.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sbg1665702735473.html\" title=\"A path is a named route to a resource required by the application, such as a database connector and database, a remote server, or a file location.\">Paths and Path Assignments</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15065e1_d15066e1_d15067e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nci1665702524490.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nci1665702524490.html\" title=\"A path-to-connector assignment describes how to access a specific resource via the appropriate network or database connector. It defines the path name, and assigns it to a configuration that specifies the connector to use, the name and location of the resource, and the credentials required to log on to it. Paths are defined in the [PATHS] section of the application assignment file.\">Path-to-Connector Assignments</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15068e1_d15069e1_d15070e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"adt1665702697363.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/adt1665702697363.html\" title=\"File assignments can be used to redirect non-DBMS files to other locations. Non-DBMS files can include Uniface UAR and XML files that Uniface controls, as well as HTML files and text files that may be used by the application. Uniface finds these files using locations listed in the [RESOURCES] assignment file section, and/or by file assignments in the [FILES] section.\">File Assignments and Redirection</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                        Configuring Applications \n                     </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15071e1_d15072e1_d15073e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ifd1665702744188.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ifd1665702744188.html\" title=\"You can configure the Uniface IDE using the ide.asn and usys.ini files.\">Configuring the Uniface IDE</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15074e1_d15075e1_d15076e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rsa1665702694240.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rsa1665702694240.html\" title=\"To configure the Uniface Router, you need to edit its assignment file, where you can define the Uniface Servers that the Uniface Router can start, and their configuration parameters.\">Configuring the Uniface Router</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15077e1_d15078e1_d15079e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ncb1665702745127.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ncb1665702745127.html\" title=\"You need to configure the Uniface Server so that it can find the databases and Uniface files, entities, and components that it needs.\">Configuring the Uniface Server</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15080e1_d15081e1_d15082e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mmb1665702745202.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mmb1665702745202.html\" title=\"Uniface automatically installs the Apache Tomcat Web Server, which is used for developing testing Uniface web applications and web services. In a production environment, you can use Tomcat as the web server for your deployed application, but you can use any Jakarta EE (Enterprise Edition) compliant web server with support for the Servlet 6.0 specification or higher.\">Configure a Web Server for Uniface Applications</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15083e1_d15084e1_d15085e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qdo1665702738098.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdo1665702738098.html\" title=\"Uniface supports the use of the TLS protocol to secure some or all communication between Uniface servers, clients, databases, and external services such as email and web services.\">Configuring Uniface Applications to Use TLS</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                        Configuration Settings Reference \n                     </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15086e1_d15087e1_d15088e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eao1665702739907.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eao1665702739907.html\" title=\"Assignment files contain assignments and settings that define the environment of a Uniface application. Assignments tell Uniface where to find the resources, connectors, servers and external components that the application needs, and how to connect to them. Assignment settings define other aspects of the application behavior.\">Configuration Settings: Assignment</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15089e1_d15090e1_d15091e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gyp1665702675022.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gyp1665702675022.html\" title=\"Initialization settings are used to configure the application on a specific platform.\">Configuration Settings: Initialization</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15092e1_d15093e1_d15094e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xvg1665702743974.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xvg1665702743974.html\" title=\"Uniface servlets run in the environment of the web application. Settings for the Uniface servlets, the WRD and SRD, are stored in the web.xml file, which is the configuration file of the web application.\">Configuration Settings: Uniface Servlet</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">For information on configuring Uniface to run on specific platforms and databases, or with other technologies, see topics in the following collections:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15095e1_d15096e1_d15097e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uya1665702742100.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uya1665702742100.html\" title=\"The installation program copies the directories, files, and executables required to run Rocket Uniface, and configures them to run out-of-the box.\">Installing Uniface</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15098e1_d15099e1_d15100e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ure1665702745274.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ure1665702745274.html\" title=\"Uniface applications are normally distributed over networked computers, with components, data, and resources located and communicating with each other by means of various types of middleware.\">Support for Distributed Applications</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15101e1_d15102e1_d15103e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ilh1665702745499.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ilh1665702745499.html\" title=\"Uniface supports TCP/IP for basic network communication and TLS/SSL for secure communication over a network or the internet. Each Uniface installation includes network connectors for both protocols, and you can configure the connections between clients and servers to use either connector, depending on your security requirements.\">Network Support</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15104e1_d15105e1_d15106e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lsp1665702531534.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsp1665702531534.html\" title=\"To access, retrieve, and store data, Uniface provides database connectors that translate Uniface I/O requests into the target database's data definition and manipulation languages.\">Database Connectors</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zhr1665702742172__li_d15107e1_d15108e1_d15109e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"juz1692183224178.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/juz1692183224178.html\" title=\"The Uniface architecture enables you to integrate Uniface and non-Uniface components in a single application, and to deploy the application on a large variety of platforms and technologies.\">Integrating with Other Technologies</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534451\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534451\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configuring Uniface and Uniface Applications Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 30, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configuring Uniface and Uniface Applications Deploying a Uniface enterprise application is largely a matter of configuring the environment to ensure that all components are running in the appropriate locations and that Uniface is able to find them. Configuration files ensure that the Uniface runtime environment can locate and initialize the application components correctly. Assignment files specify paths and protocols, and customize the application. Initialization files customize the user interface and behavior for a specific platform. The complexity of the environment determines the complexity of the configuration process. To configure Uniface on a standalone machine is much simpler than to configure a distributed environment with the Uniface Router, Uniface Server, and multiple databases, that also integrates with other technologies. The documentation in this collection describes the general use of configuration files, path assignments and redirection, and assignment settings to configure Uniface and Uniface applications. Configuration Files Configuration Files Assignment Files Initialization Settings and Files Paths to Resources Paths and Path Assignments Path-to-Connector Assignments File Assignments and Redirection Configuring Applications Configuring the Uniface IDE Configuring the Uniface Router Configuring the Uniface Server Configure a Web Server for Uniface Applications Configuring Uniface Applications to Use TLS Configuration Settings Reference Configuration Settings: Assignment Configuration Settings: Initialization Configuration Settings: Uniface Servlet For information on configuring Uniface to run on specific platforms and databases, or with other technologies, see topics in the following collections: Installing Uniface Support for Distributed Applications Network Support Database Connectors Integrating with Other Technologies Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}